   demonstrate that a huge charge-separation field can be produced when all
   the electrons are displaced from the target by the incident laser,
   resulting in a high-quality relativistic electron mirror that propagates
   against the tail of the laser pulse. The latter is efficiently reflected
   as well as compressed into an attosecond pulse that is also circularly
   polarized.}},
